{{other people||Yury Komarov (disambiguation){{!}}Yury Komarov}} {{BLP sources|date=February 2010}} [[File:Юрий Комаров.jpg|thumb]]'''Yury Alexandrovich Komarov''' (in {{lang-ru|Юрий Александрович Комаров}}, born 1945 in [[Novosibirsk]], [[Soviet Union]]) is a [[Russia]]n businessman.
In August 1996 – January 1999 he was the Director General of [[Gazexport]], export subsidiary of [[Gazprom]]. In July–August 2002 he was the acting Director General of Gazexport. From 21 January 2002 until 12 May 2005 he was a Deputy Chairman of the Management Committee of [[Gazprom]].
From October 2005 until February 2008 Komarov was a general director of Sevmorneftegaz, a subsidiary of Gazprom, which owns license to develop the [[Shtokman field|Shtokman gas field]].<ref name=highbeam> {{cite news | publisher= HighBeam Research | work = Offshore | url= http://business.highbeam.com/417112/article-1G1-168435023/july-alexander-ananenkov-gazprom-acting-ceo-yury-komarov | title = In July, Alexander Ananenkov, Gazprom's acting CEO, Yury Komarov, general director of 000 Sevmorneftegaz, and Christophe de Margerie, CEO of Total | date = 2007-08-01 | accessdate=2010-05-18}} </ref> From February 2008 to April 2010 he was a head of Shtokman Development AG, the developer of [[Shtokman field]].<ref name=upstreamonline081208> {{cite news | newspaper = [[Upstream (newspaper)|Upstream Online]] | publisher = NHST Media Group | url= http://www.upstreamonline.com/live/article167902.ece | title = Shtokman start-up hinges on credit | date = 2008-12-08 | accessdate=2010-05-18}} </ref><ref name=interfax190410> {{cite news | agency = Interfax | url= http://www.interfax.com/newsinf.asp?id=159371 | title = Shtokman Development chief Yury Komarov to step down | date = 2010-04-19 | accessdate=2010-10-31}} </ref>
Komarov is a member of the Coordination Committee of [[RosUkrEnergo]].
In March 2004 he was appointed Representative of Russia in the business advisory council of [[Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation]] forum for the 2004-2006 period by President [[Vladimir Putin]].
